  <insidersGuide><![CDATA[<p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;">Good to know</p>
<ul>
<li>Take the train for a day trip to Milan or use the ferry service to explore the quaint towns of Lake Como like Bellagio and Varenna in the central lake area</li>
<li>Ride up the Brunate funicular railway and walk to the lighthouse to take in stunning views of the lake and city skyline</li>
<li>The inventor of the cell battery, Alessandro Volta, was born and raised in Como and there is a museum dedicated to him that you can visit</li>
</ul>]]></insidersGuide>
