  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p><span><strong>The Brunate Funicular</strong> | Easy | Approx 3 hrs |<br />Since 1894, the Como-Brunate funicular railway has been taking passengers up to Brunate to enjoy the breathtaking views this vantage point offers over Lake Como and the surrounding mountains. Once at the top, you can explore the areas such as Brunate, which has the Pissarottino spring, the splendid Villa d’Este and Monte Rosa. On the way back down we pass the 15th century former convent of Eremo di San Donato.</span></p>]]></walkingDescription>
